article.headline: Grambling St. 63, Northwestern St. 62
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. -- Donald Qualls scored 25 points, including sinking a pair of free throws with 11 seconds left, to lead Grambling State in a 63-62 win over Northwestern State on Wednesday night. With the score knotted at 59-all with 2 minutes left, Dominic Knight hit one of two free throws to put Northwestern State ahead with 1:41 left to play. Neither team scored for more than a minute, until Kevin Loyd's layup put the Tigers (2-5) ahead 61-60 with 28 seconds remaining. Damon Jones couldn't convert on a layup and then a jumper to put the Demons (4-5) back ahead, and Knight's late foul put Qualls on the line to seal the win for the Tigers. Jones dropped in a layup with 3 seconds left to pull the Demons within the final margin. Loyd finished with 12 points for the Tigers, who snapped a four-game losing skid. Will Pratt paced the Demons with 15 points.
